Humans are the most widespread and politically dominant race in the known world.
They founded Midgaard and Kowloon, the twin centers of governance and commerce.
They built the Keeper road networks, raised the Great Pyramid, and established the Salt Ledger Kingdoms.
They created the Spirebound Conclave, whose failed experiments scarred the deep forest.
Their defining trait is institutional urgency: a compulsive need to create systems of law, governance, and record-keeping.
They are neither the strongest nor the most magically attuned, but they are relentless organizers and builders.
They dominate most civic, legal, and commercial institutions across the known world.
The Khenari mock their obsession with documentation.
The Deltari resent their institutional exclusions.
The Khephari and Ashborn contribute essential labor but receive no recognition.
The Umbral predate them beneath Midgaard and hold records humans discarded.
Humans are found everywhere and adapt to every environment through organization rather than innate ability.
